body:
i've updated the report with my server configuration. i'm using mysql database.
expected behaviour/actual behaviour should be obvious.

@georgehrke so i have to repair the database? how to do that?

@georgehrke i did the manual database changes as mentioned by you. at least i tried ;)
that's what i did:

    mysql> rename table oc_calendar_calendars to oc_clndr_calendars;
    mysql> rename table oc_calendar_objects to oc_clndr_objects;
    mysql> rename table oc_calendar_repeat to oc_clndr_repeat;
    mysql> rename table oc_calendar_share_calendar to oc_clndr_share_calendar;
    mysql> rename table oc_calendar_share_event to oc_clndr_share_event;
    
    mysql> update oc_appconfig set configvalue = "0.6.4" where appid = "calendar" and configkey = "installed_version";

after doing that, i was able to access the webfrontend of owncloud again! on the first view, i would also say that nothing is lost. thanks again for your quick response and help!!!

**the only question which remains is: why did the update fail in the first step? why was i able to do a manual database update, but the updater itself failed? doesn't the updater itself do the same steps?**
